  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Software trustworthy designer is in charge to integrate trustworthy features in the detailed design. He has to make&#xD;
    up the detailed design regarding the functional requirements. This expanded detailed design is used by the developer&#xD;
    himself or by another team member in order to write the source code of the component.&lt;br />&#xD;
    In order to increase trustworthiness, he has to take into account the following elements:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Trustworthiness profile&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A definition of the system with all defined external interfaces (e.g. architecture described in UML).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Technical choices and design pattern to use.(based on CSM)&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&#xD;
style=&quot;BACKGROUND: white; TEXT-ALIGN: left; MARGIN: 6pt 0cm 6pt 22.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt&quot;&#xD;
 align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot;&#xD;
    style='FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; COLOR: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB'>Use a model&#xD;
    approach with UML to refine the component definition and the different interfaces.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_PGxR8PlxEeST16WGbo409w" name="Analyze the component definition  " guid="_PGxR8PlxEeST16WGbo409w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN: 6pt 0cm; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot; style='FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB'>For the&#xD;
    component, open the architecture diagram describing the component and its interfaces (UML port notion) and check that&#xD;
    all the interfaces are defined.&lt;/span> &lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot;&#xD;
    style='FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: IT; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA'>&#xD;
    Read the functional and non-functional specifications and check that nothing is missing.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_SRW-oPlxEeST16WGbo409w" name="Design of the interfaces  " guid="_SRW-oPlxEeST16WGbo409w">
    <sectionDescription>For each functional interface, use the architecture guideline and technical choices to design them.&lt;br />&#xD;
For each non-functional interfaces (contributing to Trustworthiness), use the existing reference implementation or use the&#xD;
architecture guideline and technical choices for the new kinds. Integrate trustworthy pattern and OCL constraints answering&#xD;
non-functional trustworthiness specifications.&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot;&#xD;
style='FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; BACKGROUND: white; COLOR: black; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: IT; mso-fareast-language: IT; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA'>&#xD;
Prepare to write source code of a component.&lt;/span></purpose>
  <alternatives>&lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot;&#xD;
